{
  "stem": "8569.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "My sister, in the meantime, joined the school of nursing.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And since my father couldn't work anymore, and everybody had to register themselves in some kind of a profession, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] my father registered as a maker of wooden frames.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And as such, he got a license to open and supply the Germans with wooden photograph frames.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I have to tell you that at that time, there were already [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] transport of Jews from Warsaw into unknown places.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And only those that were quote, 'employed,' could stay.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "If you didn't have some kind of a piece of paper testifying that you are employed, you were taken.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And the first transport that were taken were the people-- were older people, sick people who came from outside of Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Those were the first transports.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I remember it must have been in 1940, '41.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "At that time, I joined the [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Polish Youth-- Jewish Polish youth group, Hashomer Hatzair.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And in 1940 or '41, two young men from Vilna, which is east Poland, came and we had a big, big conference in the big synagogue of Warsaw on Tlomackie street.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "These two young men, one of them I believe was Yehuda Wengrower.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the other one, I don't remember.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They were telling us about the atrocities that the Germans were perpetrating upon the Jews, about the mass killing of the Jews in the Vilna ghetto.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I remember that at the end of the conference when we all stood up to thank the Jewish [NON-ENGLISH], it was so strong that the walls shook.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Then I came home and I told my father about it, and my father dismissed it completely.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And said to me, don't say anything.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
